The in situ time-resolved GISAXS sputter deposition experiments with Au target were performed at the Micro-and Nanofocus X-ray scattering (MiNaXS) beamline P03 of the synchrotron source with high brilliance at PETRA III in DESY, Hamburg29. For depositing Au, an ultra-high vacuum sputter deposition apparatus RF HASE with a 99.999% Au target (from MaTecK GmbH) was used30. Au atoms were sputtered perpendicular to the sample surface under a pressure of 15 μ\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
